This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with search ranking algorithms. It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a method in the Boosting framework. Additionally, it could be categorized under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with optimization and constrained optimization problems. The paper also mentions experimental results, which suggests that it could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper could also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category as search ranking algorithms are often used in image and video search.
